    "The second group (aminoglycoside, diaminopyrimidine and tetracycline) is common in donors (Additional file 1: Fig.",
    "S10D-F and J-L).",
    "Genes from this donorassociated group may have been transferred to the recipients, resulting in greater resistome richness after FMT and their abundance did not decrease after FMT.",
    "These results highlight that the effects of FMT on the resistome vary depending on type of antibiotic and the taxa that carry the genes.",
    "Remarkable resistancesWe found a number of ESBL genes in our resistome data, and also in donor faeces."
